  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6602.15 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that level while providing buying support above the negative gamma floor at 6590. The PIN regime with 97.1B in total GEX creates a tight trading range between these key strikes, with dealers actively working to keep price pinned near current levels through mean-reverting flows. The recent GEX surge amplifies this dynamic - watch for immediate resistance at 6605-6610 and strong support at 6590, with the 6612 flip point acting as the critical regime boundary.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to stay trapped between 6590-6610 with limited breakout potential.",
